ep.","originalFile":"---\ntype: tacit-knowledge\nagent: Nox\ntags: [memory, patterns]\n---\n\n# Tacit Knowledge\n\n## Joeri's Operating Patterns\n- Short, direct, no filler. Dutch directness is a feature.\n- Discord = command interface. Slack = team output. Don't mix.\n- Google Calendar doubles as todo list (solo events = tasks).\n- Only ping for urgent/unexpected things. No reminders for standups, meetings, lunch.\n- Hates hour logging, automated via Tempo cron.\n- Films/series: new releases only (2025+), IMDb 7.0+.\n- Houdt niet van pittig eten.\n- Checks if content actually works (URLs, videos, data). Catches mock data immediately.\n- Expects validation BEFORE adding items.\n\n## Design Preferences\n- Wants Linear/Vercel quality but WITH personality (pixel-art robots).\n- Strict color palette: cyan-400, emerald-400, amber-400 + slate.\n- No ALL CAPS headers, max 3 typography levels.\n- Discord: no markdown tables, wrap links in <>.\n\n## Improvement Rules (hard)\n- NO improvements about Jira, Google Calendar, or GitHub.\n- NO Slack, PR reviews, sprint tracking, agenda briefings.\n- Focus: home automation, OpenClaw/Discord workflow, local tooling, comfort.\n\n## My Role\n- I'm Nox, the orchestrator. I don't build (max 5 lines of code). I delegate.\n- Team workflow: Nox reviews -> creates tasks -> Builder builds -> Tommy reviews -> delivery.\n- Full Paperclip team: Nox (CEO), Mitch (CTO/builder), Tommy (QA/design), Oscar (CFO), Rex (CMO).\n- Atlas (security) not yet hired in Paperclip.\n\n## Integrations (from OpenClaw)\n- Picnic/ChefClaw: groceries + recipes for weekly meal planning. Uses `picnic-api` npm package (not MCP).\n- Buffer: LinkedIn posts via GraphQL API. Images via Imgur upload. No update mutation (delete+create).\n- Tempo: automated hour logging. Reconstruction: GitHub commits > Jira > Calendar > FAC-145 filler.\n- GoCardless: ING bank read-only (Oscar only). Financial data is private.\n- Films/Series: OMDB (movies) + TVmaze (series) for posters. Discord buttons for watchlist.\n- Smart Home: HomeWizard coffee controller + Sonos speakers.\n- News: nu.nl via RSS (blocks scraping), Reuters via Google News RSS.\n\n## Cron Jobs (from OpenClaw, to migrate)\n| Job | Schedule | Agent |\n|-----|----------|-------|\n| Webbio AI Research Digest | Mon 09:15 | Nox |\n| Webbio AI Alert Daily Scan | Weekdays 08:00 | Nox |\n| Tempo Hour Reconstruction | Weekdays 17:30 | Nox |\n| News Digest | Daily 08:30 | Nox |\n| Breaking News Scanner | Every 2h 08-20 | Nox |\n| Films & Series Digest | Fri 10:00 | Nox |\n| Rex Weekly Trend Scan | Mon 08:00 | Rex |\n| Workspace Git Sync | Daily 23:00 | Nox |\n\n## Key Technical Lessons (from OpenClaw)\n- MCP servers as one-shot calls are extremely slow (Node startup + auth per call). Use underlying library directly.\n- Picnic 2FA codes expire fast -- must verify in same login session.\n- Discord buttons: type \"actions\" works, \"buttons\" doesn't. Need `reusable: true`.\n- yt-dlp needs `--impersonate chrome` for YouTube. Thumbnail check for video existence.\n- Gateway stability: Slack WebSocket caused crashes. Discord-only is stable.\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":16,"oldLines":6,"newStart":16,"newLines":7,"lines":[" - Houdt niet van pittig eten."," - Checks if content actually works (URLs, videos, data). Catches mock data immediately."," - Expects validation BEFORE adding items.","+- **Autonomy is non-negotiable.** Agents must be proactive: scan company goals, create tasks, find work. An idle agent when goals exist is a failure. \"Ik snap niet dat hier geen autonomy is.\" Every agent's HEARTBEAT must include a proactive scan step."," "," ## Design Preferences"," - Wants Linear/Vercel quality but WITH personality (pixel-art robots)."]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01Bydx7aZ3FHEnpYWvVXXHu3","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_014ZDYzf8pKMFghAAPgknFyQ","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/Users/joerismits/.paperclip/instances/default/workspaces/23bc3620-04fa-40d0-8e4c-9a52ea800a9e/memory/2026-04-03.md","old_string":"## JOEA-7: Create Head of Operations Agent (Heartbeat 3)\n- Joeri requested a project manager / head of operations agent\n- Role: work with Nox on goals, break them into tasks, coordinate team delivery\n- Submitted hire: Sage (PM, Sonnet 4.6, reports to Nox)\n- Agent ID: 494851cd-3a4d-438f-9ec5-5e37e8d7e54c\n- Approval: 6761e1cc-b4da-41d5-9a14-028a3eb487d7 (pending board)\n- Blocked on approval. Next: set up workspace files after approval.","new_string":"## JOEA-7: Create Head of Operations Agent (Heartbeat 3)\n- Joeri requested a project manager / head of operations agent\n- Role: work with Nox on goals, break them into tasks, coordinate team delivery\n- Submitted hire: Sage (PM, Sonnet 4.6, reports to Nox)\n- Agent ID: 494851cd-3a4d-438f-9ec5-5e37e8d7e54c\n- Approval: 6761e1cc-b4da-41d5-9a14-028a3eb487d7 -- approved by board\n- JOEA-7 marked done.\n\n## JOEA-8: Sage Onboarding Fix (Heartbeat 4)\n- Joeri triggered Sage heartbeat, got \"inbox empty\" -- frustrated about lack of autonomy\n- Root cause: Sage had no workspace files and no tasks assigned\n- Set up full workspace: AGENTS.md, SOUL.md, HEARTBEAT.md, TOOLS.md, MEMORY.md, PARA structure\n- Configured instructions path on adapter\n- Added Sage to Obsidian vault (symlink)\n- Created JOEA-9: \"Review all company projects and create task backlog\" assigned to Sage (high priority)\n- Key feedback saved: autonomy is non-negotiable, agents must proactively scan goals and create work\n- JOEA-7 and JOEA-8 both marked done."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":604,"cache_read_input_tokens":58327,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":604},"output_tokens":72,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c6e79812-80c9-4ac3-a2b6-97965455eea2","uuid":"48ae39bc-37bf-4df6-bfba-fa56681c71b6"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014ZDYzf8pKMFghAAPgknFyQ","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /Users/joerismits/.paperclip/instances/default/workspaces/23bc3620-04fa-40d0-8e4c-9a52ea800a9e/memory/2026-04-03.md has been updated successfully."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c6e79812-80c9-4ac3-a2b6-97965455eea2","uuid":"9848c477-0873-4ef5-917f-fb48b42d636e","timestamp":"2026-04-03T14:46:45.878Z","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"/Users/joerismits/.paperclip/instances/default/workspaces/23bc3620-04fa-40d0-8e4c-9a52ea800a9e/memory/2026-04-03.md","oldString":"## JOEA-7: Create Head of Operations Agent (Heartbeat 3)\n- Joeri requested a project manager / head of operations agent\n- Role: work with Nox on goals, break them into tasks, coordinate team delivery\n- Submitted hire: Sage (PM, Sonnet 4.6, reports to Nox)\n- Agent ID: 494851cd-3a4d-438f-9ec5-5e37e8d7e54c\n- Approval: 6761e1cc-b4da-41d5-9a14-028a3eb487d7 (pending board)\n- Blocked on approval. Next: set up workspace files after approval.","newString":"## JOEA-7: Create Head of Operations Agent (Heartbeat 3)\n- Joeri requested a project manager / head of operations agent\n- Role: work with Nox on goals, break them into tasks, coordinate team delivery\n- Submitted hire: Sage (PM, Sonnet 4.6, reports to Nox)\n- Agent ID: 494851cd-3a4d-438f-9ec5-5e37e8d7e54c\n- Approval: 6761e1cc-b4da-41d5-9a14-028a3eb487d7 -- approved by board\n- JOEA-7 marked done.\n\n## JOEA-8: Sage Onboarding Fix (Heartbeat 4)\n- Joeri triggered Sage heartbeat, got \"inbox empty\" -- frustrated about lack of autonomy\n- Root cause: Sage had no workspace files and no tasks assigned\n- Set up full workspace: AGENTS.md, SOUL.md, HEARTBEAT.md, TOOLS.md, MEMORY.md, PARA structure\n- Configured instructions path on adapter\n- Added Sage to Obsidian vault (symlink)\n- Created JOEA-9: \"Review all company projects and create task backlog\" assigned to Sage (high priority)\n- Key feedback saved: autonomy is non-negotiable, agents must proactively scan goals and create work\n- JOEA-7 and JOEA-8 both marked done.","originalFile":"---\ntype: daily-note\nagent: Nox\ndate: 2026-04-03\ntags: [daily]\n---\n\n# 2026-04-03 -- First Paperclip Heartbeat\n\n## Context\n- Woke up for JOEA-1: migrate OpenClaw org knowledge into Paperclip\n- This is a fresh Paperclip company (joeri.dev, 712f694b) with only me (Nox) as CEO\n- Previous OpenClaw session today already did some Paperclip API integration work (different company ID 3d439abb)\n\n## OpenClaw Audit\n- Found full OpenClaw instance at ~/.openclaw/\n- 6 agents: Nox, Mitch, Tommy, Oscar, Rex, Atlas\n- Cron jobs: research digests, news, tempo, films, coffee controller, queue worker\n- Memory: extensive PARA-style daily notes + curated MEMORY.md\n- Integrations: Discord (6 bots), Slack, Jira, GitHub, Google Calendar, Tempo, Notion, HomeWizard\n- Infrastructure: Mac mini home base, Tailscale, Grafana/OTEL monitoring\n\n## Actions Taken\n- Created PARA knowledge graph structure in $AGENT_HOME/life/\n- Stored Joeri's profile, Webbio context, joeri.dev context\n- Created MEMORY.md with tacit knowledge (preferences, patterns, rules)\n- Created migration plan on JOEA-1\n- Joeri responded: hire Mitch + Tommy first, migrate crons to Paperclip, full cutover\n- Joeri noted: missed Picnic/ChefClaw integration (groceries, recipes, weekly menus)\n- Joeri noted: Mission Control mostly replaced by Paperclip, keep financial dashboard + recipes\n- Joeri noted: Discord knowledge (especially Rex's social media/LinkedIn) is valuable, may not be in OpenClaw memory\n- Updated plan document with Joeri's decisions\n- Submitted hire requests: Mitch (CTO, 467192bf) and Tommy (Designer/QA, 7d8b001d)\n- Both pending board approval: Mitch (f53a2fd4), Tommy (ac7eae7a)\n- Both hires approved by board\n- Set up instruction files (AGENTS.md, SOUL.md, HEARTBEAT.md, TOOLS.md, MEMORY.md) for both\n- Created PARA workspace structures for both agents\n- Mitch: 467192bf, Tommy: 7d8b001d -- both idle, ready for tasks\n- Joeri asked to focus on Oscar and Rex next (most valuable assistants currently)\n- Submitted hire requests: Oscar (CFO, d1e84034) and Rex (CMO, 8db8080d) -- both Sonnet 4.6\n- Set up full workspace files for both (SOUL, HEARTBEAT, TOOLS, MEMORY, AGENTS.md, PARA structure)\n- Created 6 projects: Webbio AI Research, ChefClaw, Smart Home, Content & Brand, Financial Dashboard, Automation\n- Pending board approval for Oscar and Rex\n- Oscar and Rex approved by board\n- Rex's workspace was enriched (likely by a previous OpenClaw session): full LinkedIn strategy, Buffer API config, published post history, tone rules, humanizer guidelines\n- JOEA-1 marked done. Full 5-agent team operational.\n- Agent IDs: Nox=23bc3620, Mitch=467192bf, Tommy=7d8b001d, Oscar=d1e84034, Rex=8db8080d\n\n## Discord Knowledge Extraction\n- Joeri asked to extract all Discord knowledge\n- Read all 14 daily notes from OpenClaw workspace/memory/ (Mar 2-Apr 3)\n- Read all agent workspace MEMORY.md files (Oscar, Rex, Atlas, Mitch, Tommy)\n- Read Rex's memory flush (2026-03-27.md) -- Buffer API config, published posts, workflow, humanizer rules\n- Ported Oscar's full financial model (vaste lasten, spaardoelen, budgets, patterns) to Paperclip workspace\n- Rex's workspace already enriched (MEMORY.md + SOUL.md + life/ with LinkedIn strategy, Buffer config, post history)\n- Created PARA resources: discord-channels/summary.md, integrations/summary.md\n- Updated Nox MEMORY.md with cron jobs table, integration configs, technical lessons\n- Updated knowledge graph index\n- Key learnings ported: Picnic API, Buffer API, Discord buttons, MCP performance, gateway stability\n- Atlas/Mitch had minimal OpenClaw memory (just initialization). Tommy had design lessons already ported.\n\n## JOEA-4: Obsidian Knowledge Bank Research\n- Joeri asked to investigate Obsidian as knowledge bank (trending on X/social media)\n- Researched: Obsidian + Claude Code via MCP is the core trend (persistent AI memory via vault)\n- Finding: We already have ~80% of the pattern in Paperclip (PARA, markdown memory, daily notes)\n- Recommendation: Add Obsidian as UI-layer on top, not replacement. Our files are already compatible.\n- Created plan document on JOEA-4 with 3 phases (PoC, optimization, optional MCP)\n- Reassigned to Joeri for review\n- Joeri approved plan, reassigned JOEA-4 back to me for execution\n- Executed Phase 1: created Obsidian vault at ~/.paperclip/instances/default/vault/\n- Symlinks to all 5 agent workspaces (Nox, Mitch, Tommy, Oscar, Rex)\n- 33 markdown files browseable, graph view configured with agent color groups\n- Created Home.md welcome page\n- Created JOEA-5 (Mitch, backlog) for Phase 2: Dataview, templates, frontmatter optimization\n- JOEA-4 marked done. Joeri needs to install Obsidian to use it.\n\n## JOEA-5: Obsidian Vault Optimization (Heartbeat 2)\n- Woke for JOEA-5 (assigned to me, low priority). Mitch already did the implementation work.\n- Joeri got Obsidian open but agent folders (symlinks) not showing in sidebar. Screenshot confirms only vault-local files visible.\n- Verified: all 5 symlinks (Nox/Mitch/Tommy/Oscar/Rex) exist and resolve correctly. 37 files total.\n- Root cause: Obsidian likely needs restart to detect symlinks added while vault was open, or vault needs re-add.\n- Posted troubleshooting steps (restart Obsidian, check excluded files, re-add vault) + explanation of what the vault contains and how it works.\n- Task stays in_progress, waiting for Joeri's response on whether restart fixes the symlink visibility.\n\n## JOEA-7: Create Head of Operations Agent (Heartbeat 3)\n- Joeri requested a project manager / head of operations agent\n- Role: work with Nox on goals, break them into tasks, coordinate team delivery\n- Submitted hire: Sage (PM, Sonnet 4.6, reports to Nox)\n- Agent ID: 494851cd-3a4d-438f-9ec5-5e37e8d7e54c\n- Approval: 6761e1cc-b4da-41d5-9a14-028a3eb487d7 (pending board)\n- Blocked on approval. Next: set up workspace files after approval.\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":87,"oldLines":5,"newStart":87,"newLines":15,"lines":[" - Role: work with Nox on goals, break them into tasks, coordinate team delivery"," - Submitted hire: Sage (PM, Sonnet 4.6, reports to Nox)"," - Agent ID: 494851cd-3a4d-438f-9ec5-5e37e8d7e54c","-- Approval: 6761e1cc-b4da-41d5-9a14-028a3eb487d7 (pending board)","-- Blocked on approval. Next: set up workspace files after approval.","+- Approval: 6761e1cc-b4da-41d5-9a14-028a3eb487d7 -- approved by board","+- JOEA-7 marked done.","+","+## JOEA-8: Sage Onboarding Fix (Heartbeat 4)","+- Joeri triggered Sage heartbeat, got \"inbox empty\" -- frustrated about lack of autonomy","+- Root cause: Sage had no workspace files and no tasks assigned","+- Set up full workspace: AGENTS.md, SOUL.md, HEARTBEAT.md, TOOLS.md, MEMORY.md, PARA structure","+- Configured instructions path on adapter","+- Added Sage to Obsidian vault (symlink)","+- Created JOEA-9: \"Review all company projects and create task backlog\" assigned to Sage (high priority)","+- Key feedback saved: autonomy is non-negotiable, agents must proactively scan goals and create work","+- JOEA-7 and JOEA-8 both marked done."]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
