{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01QRgUqiik9HfBcBChvSyL94","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01DJsiK3SuCcgjn9bUNiPTZ7","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/Users/joerismits/.paperclip/instances/default/workspaces/23bc3620-04fa-40d0-8e4c-9a52ea800a9e/memory/2026-04-03.md","old_string":"- Key learnings ported: Picnic API, Buffer API, Discord buttons, MCP performance, gateway stability\n- Atlas/Mitch had minimal OpenClaw memory (just initialization). Tommy had design lessons already ported.","new_string":"- Key learnings ported: Picnic API, Buffer API, Discord buttons, MCP performance, gateway stability\n- Atlas/Mitch had minimal OpenClaw memory (just initialization). Tommy had design lessons already ported.\n\n## JOEA-4: Obsidian Knowledge Bank Research\n- Joeri asked to investigate Obsidian as knowledge bank (trending on X/social media)\n- Researched: Obsidian + Claude Code via MCP is the core trend (persistent AI memory via vault)\n- Finding: We already have ~80% of the pattern in Paperclip (PARA, markdown memory, daily notes)\n- Recommendation: Add Obsidian as UI-layer on top, not replacement. Our files are already compatible.\n- Created plan document on JOEA-4 with 3 phases (PoC, optimization, optional MCP)\n- Reassigned to Joeri for review"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":263,"cache_read_input_tokens":42902,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":263},"output_tokens":65,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e9d27f8b-6297-46fe-a009-7e7fb66e07a4","uuid":"e2dcae3c-576e-4d8b-9ccf-43e16f56614c"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DJsiK3SuCcgjn9bUNiPTZ7","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /Users/joerismits/.paperclip/instances/default/workspaces/23bc3620-04fa-40d0-8e4c-9a52ea800a9e/memory/2026-04-03.md has been updated successfully."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e9d27f8b-6297-46fe-a009-7e7fb66e07a4","uuid":"65f2cfe7-e666-4c95-af8a-1dd6b238e3c5","timestamp":"2026-04-03T13:22:53.092Z","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"/Users/joerismits/.paperclip/instances/default/workspaces/23bc3620-04fa-40d0-8e4c-9a52ea800a9e/memory/2026-04-03.md","oldString":"- Key learnings ported: Picnic API, Buffer API, Discord buttons, MCP performance, gateway stability\n- Atlas/Mitch had minimal OpenClaw memory (just initialization). Tommy had design lessons already ported.","newString":"- Key learnings ported: Picnic API, Buffer API, Discord buttons, MCP performance, gateway stability\n- Atlas/Mitch had minimal OpenClaw memory (just initialization). Tommy had design lessons already ported.\n\n## JOEA-4: Obsidian Knowledge Bank Research\n- Joeri asked to investigate Obsidian as knowledge bank (trending on X/social media)\n- Researched: Obsidian + Claude Code via MCP is the core trend (persistent AI memory via vault)\n- Finding: We already have ~80% of the pattern in Paperclip (PARA, markdown memory, daily notes)\n- Recommendation: Add Obsidian as UI-layer on top, not replacement. Our files are already compatible.\n- Created plan document on JOEA-4 with 3 phases (PoC, optimization, optional MCP)\n- Reassigned to Joeri for review","originalFile":"# 2026-04-03 -- First Paperclip Heartbeat\n\n## Context\n- Woke up for JOEA-1: migrate OpenClaw org knowledge into Paperclip\n- This is a fresh Paperclip company (joeri.dev, 712f694b) with only me (Nox) as CEO\n- Previous OpenClaw session today already did some Paperclip API integration work (different company ID 3d439abb)\n\n## OpenClaw Audit\n- Found full OpenClaw instance at ~/.openclaw/\n- 6 agents: Nox, Mitch, Tommy, Oscar, Rex, Atlas\n- Cron jobs: research digests, news, tempo, films, coffee controller, queue worker\n- Memory: extensive PARA-style daily notes + curated MEMORY.md\n- Integrations: Discord (6 bots), Slack, Jira, GitHub, Google Calendar, Tempo, Notion, HomeWizard\n- Infrastructure: Mac mini home base, Tailscale, Grafana/OTEL monitoring\n\n## Actions Taken\n- Created PARA knowledge graph structure in $AGENT_HOME/life/\n- Stored Joeri's profile, Webbio context, joeri.dev context\n- Created MEMORY.md with tacit knowledge (preferences, patterns, rules)\n- Created migration plan on JOEA-1\n- Joeri responded: hire Mitch + Tommy first, migrate crons to Paperclip, full cutover\n- Joeri noted: missed Picnic/ChefClaw integration (groceries, recipes, weekly menus)\n- Joeri noted: Mission Control mostly replaced by Paperclip, keep financial dashboard + recipes\n- Joeri noted: Discord knowledge (especially Rex's social media/LinkedIn) is valuable, may not be in OpenClaw memory\n- Updated plan document with Joeri's decisions\n- Submitted hire requests: Mitch (CTO, 467192bf) and Tommy (Designer/QA, 7d8b001d)\n- Both pending board approval: Mitch (f53a2fd4), Tommy (ac7eae7a)\n- Both hires approved by board\n- Set up instruction files (AGENTS.md, SOUL.md, HEARTBEAT.md, TOOLS.md, MEMORY.md) for both\n- Created PARA workspace structures for both agents\n- Mitch: 467192bf, Tommy: 7d8b001d -- both idle, ready for tasks\n- Joeri asked to focus on Oscar and Rex next (most valuable assistants currently)\n- Submitted hire requests: Oscar (CFO, d1e84034) and Rex (CMO, 8db8080d) -- both Sonnet 4.6\n- Set up full workspace files for both (SOUL, HEARTBEAT, TOOLS, MEMORY, AGENTS.md, PARA structure)\n- Created 6 projects: Webbio AI Research, ChefClaw, Smart Home, Content & Brand, Financial Dashboard, Automation\n- Pending board approval for Oscar and Rex\n- Oscar and Rex approved by board\n- Rex's workspace was enriched (likely by a previous OpenClaw session): full LinkedIn strategy, Buffer API config, published post history, tone rules, humanizer guidelines\n- JOEA-1 marked done. Full 5-agent team operational.\n- Agent IDs: Nox=23bc3620, Mitch=467192bf, Tommy=7d8b001d, Oscar=d1e84034, Rex=8db8080d\n\n## Discord Knowledge Extraction\n- Joeri asked to extract all Discord knowledge\n- Read all 14 daily notes from OpenClaw workspace/memory/ (Mar 2-Apr 3)\n- Read all agent workspace MEMORY.md files (Oscar, Rex, Atlas, Mitch, Tommy)\n- Read Rex's memory flush (2026-03-27.md) -- Buffer API config, published posts, workflow, humanizer rules\n- Ported Oscar's full financial model (vaste lasten, spaardoelen, budgets, patterns) to Paperclip workspace\n- Rex's workspace already enriched (MEMORY.md + SOUL.md + life/ with LinkedIn strategy, Buffer config, post history)\n- Created PARA resources: discord-channels/summary.md, integrations/summary.md\n- Updated Nox MEMORY.md with cron jobs table, integration configs, technical lessons\n- Updated knowledge graph index\n- Key learnings ported: Picnic API, Buffer API, Discord buttons, MCP performance, gateway stability\n- Atlas/Mitch had minimal OpenClaw memory (just initialization). Tommy had design lessons already ported.\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":51,"oldLines":3,"newStart":51,"newLines":11,"lines":[" - Updated knowledge graph index"," - Key learnings ported: Picnic API, Buffer API, Discord buttons, MCP performance, gateway stability"," - Atlas/Mitch had minimal OpenClaw memory (just initialization). Tommy had design lessons already ported.","+","+## JOEA-4: Obsidian Knowledge Bank Research","+- Joeri asked to investigate Obsidian as knowledge bank (trending on X/social media)","+- Researched: Obsidian + Claude Code via MCP is the core trend (persistent AI memory via vault)","+- Finding: We already have ~80% of the pattern in Paperclip (PARA, markdown memory, daily notes)","+- Recommendation: Add Obsidian as UI-layer on top, not replacement. Our files are already compatible.","+- Created plan document on JOEA-4 with 3 phases (PoC, optimization, optional MCP)","+- Reassigned to Joeri for review"]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01KjsAXJ6S27M1rdHqGBMSyg","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Done. Here's what I did on **JOEA-4**:\n\n**Research completed** ŌĆö the Obsidian-as-knowledge-bank trend is real and specifically about Obsidian + Claude Code via MCP for persistent AI memory.\n\n**Key finding**: We already have ~80% of this pattern built in Paperclip (PARA structure, markdown memory, daily notes, persistent agent context). What we're missing is the **human-facing UI** ŌĆö graph view, backlinks, visual search.\n\n**Recommendation**: Add Obsidian as a UI-layer on top of our existing workspace files. No migration needed ŌĆö our markdown files are already Obsidian-compatible. Phase 1 is literally \"open the workspace folder as an Obsidian vault.\"\n\nFull plan with implementation phases, risks, and trade-offs is on [JOEA-4](/JOEA/issues/JOEA-4#document-plan). Reassigned to Joeri for review."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":492,"cache_read_input_tokens":43165,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":492},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e9d27f8b-6297-46fe-a009-7e7fb66e07a4","uuid":"9737ea9c-aefd-4e5e-9753-e9b40c426b74"}
