{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01J77nGog9AqEnuqyn4YAfmJ","type":"tool_result","content":"# Obsidian Skills Project Summary\n\n**What it is:** This is a collection of agent skills enabling AI assistants (like Claude Code and Codex CLI) to work with Obsidian, a note-taking application.\n\n**What it does:** The project provides five specialized skills that teach agents to:\n- Create and edit Obsidian Markdown files with advanced syntax\n- Work with Obsidian Bases for structured data\n- Manipulate JSON Canvas files for visual connections\n- Interact with Obsidian through its command-line interface\n- Extract clean markdown from web pages using Defuddle\n\n**Subscription requirements:** No. The project is open-source under MIT license and works with free or paid Obsidian installations. Agents using these skills require their own access to compatible AI tools (Claude Code, Codex CLI, or OpenCode).\n\n**Requirements:** Users need either Obsidian installed locally or a compatible agent framework, plus one of several installation methods (plugin marketplace, npm package, or manual setup). The skills follow industry standards, making them compatible across different agent platforms."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8e091eb8-9d61-4487-ae34-1e20746dabd3","uuid":"4a82df6d-87fc-4818-b04d-c8d39ac8c99b","timestamp":"2026-04-03T13:39:51.292Z","tool_use_result":{"bytes":261554,"code":200,"codeText":"OK","result":"# Obsidian Skills Project Summary\n\n**What it is:** This is a collection of agent skills enabling AI assistants (like Claude Code and Codex CLI) to work with Obsidian, a note-taking application.\n\n**What it does:** The project provides five specialized skills that teach agents to:\n- Create and edit Obsidian Markdown files with advanced syntax\n- Work with Obsidian Bases for structured data\n- Manipulate JSON Canvas files for visual connections\n- Interact with Obsidian through its command-line interface\n- Extract clean markdown from web pages using Defuddle\n\n**Subscription requirements:** No. The project is open-source under MIT license and works with free or paid Obsidian installations. Agents using these skills require their own access to compatible AI tools (Claude Code, Codex CLI, or OpenCode).\n\n**Requirements:** Users need either Obsidian installed locally or a compatible agent framework, plus one of several installation methods (plugin marketplace, npm package, or manual setup). The skills follow industry standards, making them compatible across different agent platforms.","durationMs":4123,"url":"https://github.com/kepano/obsidian-skills"}}
