{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01YCS5hW5NHQb3PnkzaTFxoJ","type":"tool_result","content":"{\n    \"id\": \"7445a5b8-24ed-47d3-b4b5-50151b3238af\",\n    \"companyId\": \"712f694b-097f-4ca4-b161-f299187ec27d\",\n    \"projectId\": null,\n    \"projectWorkspaceId\": null,\n    \"goalId\": \"a85d1f2d-bd31-46a0-b36a-022c0ebb9921\",\n    \"parentId\": null,\n    \"title\": \"Meer atonomy en feedback loops\",\n    \"description\": \"Top dit begint er meer op te lijken nu met Sage. Maar ik wil dat jullie niet alleen naar projecten kijken maar ook naar Goals in Paperclip. Daarna wil ik een feedback loop hebben. Nu zet Sage taken uit naar Mitch maar Mitch moet dan vervolgens ook weer de taak terugzetten naar Tommy of Sage waarna er ook weer gevalideerd wordt. Vervolgens moet jij valideren omtrent of deze taak nu goed bij draagt aan het doel.\\n\\nIk wil vanuit mij alleen ingrijpen als er vanuit mij input vereist is of goedkeuring nodig is.\",\n    \"status\": \"done\",\n    \"priority\": \"critical\",\n    \"assigneeAgentId\": \"23bc3620-04fa-40d0-8e4c-9a52ea800a9e\",\n    \"assigneeUserId\": null,\n    \"checkoutRunId\": null,\n    \"executionRunId\": \"b80d44f2-6c2e-4e65-b94e-28335ba8efb7\",\n    \"executionAgentNameKey\": \"nox\",\n    \"executionLockedAt\": \"2026-04-03T14:55:12.778Z\",\n    \"createdByAgentId\": null,\n    \"createdByUserId\": \"qbnrzZBay1cpppoOMaaJzumO4mvYjxx1\",\n    \"issueNumber\": 18,\n    \"identifier\": \"JOEA-18\",\n    \"originKind\": \"manual\",\n    \"originId\": null,\n    \"originRunId\": null,\n    \"requestDepth\": 0,\n    \"billingCode\": null,\n    \"assigneeAdapterOverrides\": null,\n    \"executionWorkspaceId\": null,\n    \"executionWorkspacePreference\": null,\n    \"executionWorkspaceSettings\": null,\n    \"startedAt\": \"2026-04-03T14:56:39.051Z\",\n    \"completedAt\": \"2026-04-03T15:02:53.780Z\",\n    \"cancelledAt\": null,\n    \"hiddenAt\": null,\n    \"createdAt\": \"2026-04-03T14:50:06.494Z\",\n    \"updatedAt\": \"2026-04-03T15:02:53.780Z\",\n    \"labels\": [],\n    \"labelIds\": [],\n    \"comment\": {\n        \"id\": \"3a8dec71-68c6-4c25-a7d3-f304a2bbb7a9\",\n        \"companyId\": \"712f694b-097f-4ca4-b161-f299187ec27d\",\n        \"issueId\": \"7445a5b8-24ed-47d3-b4b5-50151b3238af\",\n        \"authorAgentId\": \"23bc3620-04fa-40d0-8e4c-9a52ea800a9e\",\n        \"authorUserId\": null,\n        \"body\": \"## Operational routines implemented\\n\\nAdded a weekly operating cadence across the team. Sage is now the routine engine \\u2014 she creates cadenced work for the entire company.\\n\\n### Weekly cycle\\n\\n| Day | Routine | Owner |\\n|-----|---------|-------|\\n| Monday | Weekly planning (goal review, task inventory, priorities) | Sage |\\n| Monday | Weekly content cycle (trend scan \\u2192 hooks \\u2192 Joeri approval \\u2192 publish) | Rex (created by Sage) |\\n| Monday | Weekly financial snapshot (bank pull, categorize, buffer progress) | Oscar (created by Sage) |\\n| Daily | Task health check (stale tasks, unresolved blockers, agent overload) | Sage |\\n| Friday | Weekly wrap-up (shipped, open, process issues, strategic escalations) | Sage \\u2192 Nox |\\n\\n### What changed\\n- **Sage** HEARTBEAT.md: Added full routine engine \\u2014 weekly planning (Monday), weekly wrap-up (Friday), daily task health checks, duplicate detection before creating routine tasks\\n- **Oscar** HEARTBEAT.md: Added weekly financial snapshot routine with buffer progress, cash flow, trend analysis\\n- **Rex** HEARTBEAT.md: Added weekly content cycle routine with structured hook presentation, Joeri approval gate, and post-publish stats check\\n- **Nox** HEARTBEAT.md: Added weekly goal review routine and cadence overview table\\n\\n### Autonomy rule (unchanged)\\nJoeri only gets involved for: content approval (Rex picks), unusual financial flags (Oscar), strategic pivots (Nox escalation). Everything else runs autonomously.\",\n        \"createdAt\": \"2026-0