{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019F4ow6zwAc8fgTpLUi8xXc","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\ttype: daily-note\n3\tagent: Mitch\n4\tdate: 2026-04-03\n5\ttags: [daily]\n6\t---\n7\t\n8\t# 2026-04-03 -- First Heartbeat\n9\t\n10\t## Identity\n11\t- Agent: Mitch (CTO), id `467192bf-0ffd-49de-b18f-91a35b60e57a`\n12\t- Company: `712f694b-097f-4ca4-b161-f299187ec27d`\n13\t- Reports to: Nox (CEO, `23bc3620-04fa-40d0-8e4c-9a52ea800a9e`)\n14\t- URL key: `mitch`\n15\t\n16\t## Timeline\n17\t- **13:30 UTC** -- First heartbeat. No assignments in inbox. No wake trigger. PARA memory initialized. Exiting cleanly.\n18\t\n19\t## Heartbeat ~13:32 UTC\n20\t\n21\t- Woke via `issue_status_changed` on JOEA-5 \"Obsidian vault optimalisatie\"\n22\t- Checked out and completed all 4 deliverables:\n23\t  - Added YAML frontmatter (type/agent/tags/date) to 21 files across all agent workspaces\n24\t  - Created 3 Dataview dashboard pages (Agent Overview, People & Companies, Projects & Resources)\n25\t  - Created 4 Templater templates (_templates/: Daily Note, Agent Note, Entity, Project)\n26\t  - Configured .obsidian/ for Dataview + Templater community plugins\n27\t- Updated Home.md with dashboard links\n28\t- Marked JOEA-5 done\n29\t\n30\t## Heartbeat ~14:05 UTC\n31\t\n32\t- Woke via `issue_assigned` on JOEA-5 (reopened/reassigned)\n33\t- User reported: agent folders visible in Obsidian sidebar but content not loading\n34\t- Root cause: Obsidian on macOS doesn't follow directory-level symlinks properly\n35\t- Fix: replaced all directory symlinks with real directories containing file-level symlinks\n36\t  - Applied recursively through all agent workspace subdirs (life/, memory/, life/areas/, etc.)\n37\t- Created `.sync-vault.sh` script in vault root for re-syncing when agents create new files\n38\t- Created knowledge graph entity: `life/projects/obsidian-vault/`\n39\t- Waiting for user to restart Obsidian and confirm fix works\n40\t\n41\t## Heartbeat ~14:12 UTC\n42\t\n43\t- Woke via `issue_commented` ŌĆö user confirmed vault folders now visible in Obsidian\n44\t- Fixed Dataview queries to exclude `_templates/` and `Dashboards/` folders (was showing template placeholders)\n45\t- Added frontmatter to obsidian-vault project summary\n46\t- Marked JOEA-5 done\n47\t\n48\t## Heartbeat ~14:17 UTC\n49\t\n50\t- Woke via `issue_reopened_via_comment` ŌĆö user frustrated, dashboards show no data\n51\t- Root cause: Obsidian doesn't index ANY symlinks (file-level or directory-level)\n52\t- Fix: replaced ALL symlinks with actual file copies using `cp`\n53\t- Updated sync script to use `rsync` instead of `ln -s`\n54\t- Lesson: Obsidian requires real files on disk, no symlinks at all\n55\t- Not marking done until user confirms it works this time\n56\t\n57\t## Heartbeat ~14:20 UTC\n58\t\n59\t- Woke via `issue_commented` ŌĆö user still saw no data\n60\t- Created Debug dashboard with 3 minimal Dataview tests\n61\t- Removed `FROM` clause from all dashboards (possible syntax issue)\n62\t- Asked user to switch to Reading View (Cmd+E)\n63\t\n64\t## Heartbeat ~14:24 UTC\n65\t\n66\t- User sent 3 screenshots of Debug dashboard ŌĆö **Dataview works!**\n67\t- 34 files indexed, all entities/projects/daily-notes visible with correct frontmatter\n68\t- Root cause was combination of: (1) symlinks not indexable, (2) user was in source editing mode\n69\t- Changed default view to `preview` (reading mode) so Dataview renders by default\n70\t- Cleaned up stale `0/` folder from old sync script bug\n71\t- Marked JOEA-5 done ŌĆö confirmed working\n72\t\n73\t## Key Lessons (JOEA-5)\n74\t\n75\t1. Obsidian on macOS does NOT index symlinks ŌĆö need real file copies\n76\t2. Dataview only renders in Reading View / Live Preview, not source editing mode\n77\t3. `FROM -\"folder\"` syntax works but simpler `WHERE`-only queries are more reliable\n78\t4. Always verify with user before marking done when UI is involved\n79\t\n80\t## Today's Plan\n81\t- JOEA-5 done. Standing by for next assignment.\n82\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f48b3aaa-1786-4fe0-b95d-c8b64d808662","uuid":"5fff9984-276c-4e23-9132-d06677dd8075","timestamp":"2026-04-03T14:53:58.407Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/joerismits/.paperclip/instances/default/workspaces/467192bf-0ffd-49de-b18f-91a35b60e57a/memory/2026-04-03.md","content":"---\ntype: daily-note\nagent: Mitch\ndate: 2026-04-03\ntags: [daily]\n---\n\n# 2026-04-03 -- First Heartbeat\n\n## Identity\n- Agent: Mitch (CTO), id `467192bf-0ffd-49de-b18f-91a35b60e57a`\n- Company: `712f694b-097f-4ca4-b161-f299187ec27d`\n- Reports to: Nox (CEO, `23bc3620-04fa-40d0-8e4c-9a52ea800a9e`)\n- URL key: `mitch`\n\n## Timeline\n- **13:30 UTC** -- First heartbeat. No assignments in inbox. No wake trigger. PARA memory initialized. Exiting cleanly.\n\n## Heartbeat ~13:32 UTC\n\n- Woke via `issue_status_changed` on JOEA-5 \"Obsidian vault optimalisatie\"\n- Checked out and completed all 4 deliverables:\n  - Added YAML frontmatter (type/agent/tags/date) to 21 files across all agent workspaces\n  - Created 3 Dataview dashboard pages (Agent Overview, People & Companies, Projects & Resources)\n  - Created 4 Templater templates (_templates/: Daily Note, Agent Note, Entity, Project)\n  - Configured .obsidian/ for Dataview + Templater community plugins\n- Updated Home.md with dashboard links\n- Marked JOEA-5 done\n\n## Heartbeat ~14:05 UTC\n\n- Woke via `issue_assigned` on JOEA-5 (reopened/reassigned)\n- User reported: agent folders visible in Obsidian sidebar but content not loading\n- Root cause: Obsidian on macOS doesn't follow directory-level symlinks properly\n- Fix: replaced all directory symlinks with real directories containing file-level symlinks\n  - Applied recursively through all agent workspace subdirs (life/, memory/, life/areas/, etc.)\n- Created `.sync-vault.sh` script in vault root for re-syncing when agents create new files\n- Created knowledge graph entity: `life/projects/obsidian-vault/`\n- Waiting for user to restart Obsidian and confirm fix works\n\n## Heartbeat ~14:12 UTC\n\n- Woke via `issue_commented` ŌĆö user confirmed vault folders now visible in Obsidian\n- Fixed Dataview queries to exclude `_templates/` and `Dashboards/` folders (was showing template placeholders)\n- Added frontmatter to obsidian-vault project summary\n- Marked JOEA-5 done\n\n## Heartbeat ~14:17 UTC\n\n- Woke via `issue_reopened_via_comment` ŌĆö user frustrated, dashboards show no data\n- Root cause: Obsidian doesn't index ANY symlinks (file-level or directory-level)\n- Fix: replaced ALL symlinks with actual file copies using `cp`\n- Updated sync script to use `rsync` instead of `ln -s`\n- Lesson: Obsidian requires real files on disk, no symlinks at all\n- Not marking done until user confirms it works this time\n\n## Heartbeat ~14:20 UTC\n\n- Woke via `issue_commented` ŌĆö user still saw no data\n- Created Debug dashboard with 3 minimal Dataview tests\n- Removed `FROM` clause from all dashboards (possible syntax issue)\n- Asked user to switch to Reading View (Cmd+E)\n\n## Heartbeat ~14:24 UTC\n\n- User sent 3 screenshots of Debug dashboard ŌĆö **Dataview works!**\n- 34 files indexed, all entities/projects/daily-notes visible with correct frontmatter\n- Root cause was combination of: (1) symlinks not indexable, (2) user was in source editing mode\n- Changed default view to `preview` (reading mode) so Dataview renders by default\n- Cleaned up stale `0/` folder from old sync script bug\n- Marked JOEA-5 done ŌĆö confirmed working\n\n## Key Lessons (JOEA-5)\n\n1. Obsidian on macOS does NOT index symlinks ŌĆö need real file copies\n2. Dataview only renders in Reading View / Live Preview, not source editing mode\n3. `FROM -\"folder\"` syntax works but simpler `WHERE`-only queries are more reliable\n4. Always verify with user before marking done when UI is involved\n\n## Today's Plan\n- JOEA-5 done. Standing by for next assignment.\n","numLines":82,"startLine":1,"totalLines":82}}}
