{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Q498T7e6eURTYCj7EthuaG","type":"tool_result","content":"{\n    \"id\": \"7445a5b8-24ed-47d3-b4b5-50151b3238af\",\n    \"companyId\": \"712f694b-097f-4ca4-b161-f299187ec27d\",\n    \"projectId\": null,\n    \"projectWorkspaceId\": null,\n    \"goalId\": \"a85d1f2d-bd31-46a0-b36a-022c0ebb9921\",\n    \"parentId\": null,\n    \"title\": \"Meer atonomy en feedback loops\",\n    \"description\": \"Top dit begint er meer op te lijken nu met Sage. Maar ik wil dat jullie niet alleen naar projecten kijken maar ook naar Goals in Paperclip. Daarna wil ik een feedback loop hebben. Nu zet Sage taken uit naar Mitch maar Mitch moet dan vervolgens ook weer de taak terugzetten naar Tommy of Sage waarna er ook weer gevalideerd wordt. Vervolgens moet jij valideren omtrent of deze taak nu goed bij draagt aan het doel.\\n\\nIk wil vanuit mij alleen ingrijpen als er vanuit mij input vereist is of goedkeuring nodig is.\",\n    \"status\": \"done\",\n    \"priority\": \"critical\",\n    \"assigneeAgentId\": \"23bc3620-04fa-40d0-8e4c-9a52ea800a9e\",\n    \"assigneeUserId\": null,\n    \"checkoutRunId\": null,\n    \"executionRunId\": \"07da96e0-f46a-408a-8016-e6e012c42446\",\n    \"executionAgentNameKey\": \"nox\",\n    \"executionLockedAt\": \"2026-04-03T15:04:38.711Z\",\n    \"createdByAgentId\": null,\n    \"createdByUserId\": \"qbnrzZBay1cpppoOMaaJzumO4mvYjxx1\",\n    \"issueNumber\": 18,\n    \"identifier\": \"JOEA-18\",\n    \"originKind\": \"manual\",\n    \"originId\": null,\n    \"originRunId\": null,\n    \"requestDepth\": 0,\n    \"billingCode\": null,\n    \"assigneeAdapterOverrides\": null,\n    \"executionWorkspaceId\": null,\n    \"executionWorkspacePreference\": null,\n    \"executionWorkspaceSettings\": null,\n    \"startedAt\": \"2026-04-03T15:05:12.059Z\",\n    \"completedAt\": \"2026-04-03T15:05:57.643Z\",\n    \"cancelledAt\": null,\n    \"hiddenAt\": null,\n    \"createdAt\": \"2026-04-03T14:50:06.494Z\",\n    \"updatedAt\": \"2026-04-03T15:05:57.643Z\",\n    \"labels\": [],\n    \"labelIds\": [],\n    \"comment\": {\n        \"id\": \"6cefbdf0-94c7-4032-9eab-293c0c16daae\",\n        \"companyId\": \"712f694b-097f-4ca4-b161-f299187ec27d\",\n        \"issueId\": \"7445a5b8-24ed-47d3-b4b5-50151b3238af\",\n        \"authorAgentId\": \"23bc3620-04fa-40d0-8e4c-9a52ea800a9e\",\n        \"authorUserId\": null,\n        \"body\": \"## Routines now live in Paperclip\\n\\nJe had gelijk \\u2014 instructies zonder taken betekent stilstaande agents. Opgelost.\\n\\n### Created this week's routine tasks\\n- [JOEA-20](/JOEA/issues/JOEA-20) \\u2014 **Sage**: Weekly planning (goal review, task inventory, priorities)\\n- [JOEA-21](/JOEA/issues/JOEA-21) \\u2014 **Oscar**: Weekly financial snapshot (bank data, buffer progress, cash flow)\\n- [JOEA-22](/JOEA/issues/JOEA-22) \\u2014 **Rex**: Weekly content cycle (trend scan \\u2192 hooks \\u2192 Joeri approval \\u2192 publish)\\n\\nAll three are assigned and will trigger heartbeats. Sage, Oscar, and Rex will wake up and execute.\\n\\n### How the cycle sustains itself\\nSage's HEARTBEAT.md now includes the routine engine: every Monday she checks if routine tasks exist for the current week and creates them if missing. This means the cycle self-perpetuates \\u2014 I don't need to manually create them each week.\\n\\n### Daily involvement\\nSage runs a daily task health check on every heartbeat:\\n- Flags tasks in_progress >24h without updates\\n- Escalates unresolved blockers to me\\n- Redistributes if any agent is overloaded\\n\\nFriday wrap-up comes to me for strategic review before the next week kicks off.\",\n        \"createdAt\": \"2026-04-03T15:05:57.647Z\",\n        \"updatedAt\": \"2026-04-03T15:05:57.647Z\"\n    }\n}","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8562baa3-58e2-42cb-ab9d-4fa13b8c7a66","uuid":"109cebd5-d427-4c4f-906e-eec76164867d","timestamp":"2026-04-03T15:05:57.673Z","tool_use_result":{"stdo