on":true,"outputTokens":4997,"sessionReused":false,"rawInputTokens":19,"sessionRotated":false,"rawOutputTokens":4997,"cachedInputTokens":375689,"taskSessionReused":false,"persistedSessionId":"808108e8-5f77-4c63-a64b-a1ed27ddfc09","rawCachedInputTokens":375689,"sessionRotationReason":null}$paperclip$, $paperclip${"type":"result","uuid":"afe6b9fa-b0a8-4e06-8bf7-ee4d1d358a80","usage":{"speed":"standard","iterations":[],"input_tokens":19,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"","output_tokens":4997,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":29949,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"server_tool_use":{"web_fetch_requests":0,"web_search_requests":0},"cache_read_input_tokens":375689,"cache_creation_input_tokens":29949},"result":"Heartbeat complete.\n\n**[JOEA-22](/JOEA/issues/JOEA-22) ŌĆö Weekly content cycle**\n\n- Trend scan done: 3 hooks gepost in Dutch covering MCP 2026 roadmap, Dutch Digital Service (coalitieakkoord), en GenAI in NL overheid (8ŌåÆ81 apps)\n- Task geblokkeerd, terug naar Joeri ŌĆö hij moet ├®├®n hook kiezen + 2-3 zinnen eigen take geven\n- Daarna schrijf ik de volledige post en zet hem klaar als Buffer draft","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"num_turns":23,"modelUsage":{"claude-sonnet-4-6":{"costUSD":0.38790945000000004,"inputTokens":939,"outputTokens":6670,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000,"webSearchRequests":0,"cacheReadInputTokens":432929,"cacheCreationInputTokens":41377},"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"costUSD":0.20018249999999999,"inputTokens":14230,"outputTokens":3149,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000,"webSearchRequests":6,"cacheReadInputTokens":0,"cacheCreationInputTokens":88166}},"session_id":"808108e8-5f77-4c63-a64b-a1ed27ddfc09","duration_ms":195961,"stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0.5880919499999999,"duration_api_ms":218758,"fast_mode_state":"off","permission_denials":[]}$paperclip$, NULL, $paperclip$808108e8-5f77-4c63-a64b-a1ed27ddfc09$paperclip$, $paperclip$local_file$paperclip$, $paperclip$712f694b-097f-4ca4-b161-f299187ec27d/8db8080d-9064-4707-99c2-2e8d186f5e17/e548d79f-968f-42fc-8679-51deac627408.ndjson$paperclip$, $paperclip$179745$paperclip$, $paperclip$bad0003d8610b8f033b8a89002ae6faaf11e217fa8cfa68e2e914d2ed45b2ebb$paperclip$, false, $paperclip$to 2026-04-03:\n\n---\n\n## Tech News Briefing ŌĆö Week of 30 March ŌĆō 3 April 2026\n\n---\n\n**1. Frontier model war: GPT-5.4, Gemini 3.1, and Claude updates all land in March**\n\nOpenAI shipped GPT-5.4 (March 5) with record scores on computer-use and knowledge-work benchmarks ŌĆö API pricing at $2.50/M input tokens for the standard tier. Google countered with Gemini 3.1 Pro, which leads 13 of 16 major benchmarks and runs at roughly one-third of GPT-5.4's API cost due to a new compression algorithm that cuts memory needs sixfold. Anthropic's Claude Sonnet 4.6 (the model powering this response) is currently topping the GDPval-AA Elo leaderboard, performing at near-Opus quality at Sonnet pricing ŌĆö directly relevant for cost-efficient agentic workloads.\n\n---\n\n**2. MCP ecosystem crosses 6,400 registered servers ŌĆö 2026 roadmap focuses on enterprise readiness**\n\nThe Model Context Protocol now has over 6,400 servers in its official registry and is running in production at enterprises at scale. The published 2026 roadmap addresses gaps that matter for production agentic systems: better Streamable HTTP for remote server deployments (load balancer compatibility, session handling), improved Task primitive lifecycle semantics (retry, expiry), and enterprise requirements like audit trails, SSO-integrated auth, and gateway configuration portability. For anyone building orchestration layers on top of MCP, the direction is clear: the protocol is moving from prototype to production-grade infrastructure.\n\n---\n\n**3. GitHub Copilot agent mode reaches GA across VS Code and JetBrains; Cursor ships Composer 2**\n\nCopilot's agent mode is now generally available in VS Code and JetBrains, and agentic code review shipped in March ŌĆö it can now act on review feedback autonomously. Separately, Cursor shipped Composer 2 on March 19, built on Moonshot AI's Kimi K2.5 with heavy reinforcement learning fine-tuning; it's Cursor's bet that purpose-built coding models beat general LLMs on dev tasks. The emerging developer consensus in 2026: Cursor for daily editing, Claude Code for complex multi-file work and delegation-style tasks.\n\n---\n\n**4. Dutch 2026 coalition agreement: digital sovereignty and a new Dutch Digital Service**\n\nThe new Dutch coalition agreement (presented this week) puts digital autonomy front and center, including a mandate to establish a **Dutch Digital Service** ŌĆö a central body with enforcement power over government ICT choices. This is a direct response to dependency on US hyperscalers and fragmented government IT. For public sector tech leads in the Arnhem-Nijmegen region, this signals upcoming procurement and architecture shifts, particularly around cloud strategy and open-source alignment.\n\n---\n\n**5. Dutch government generative AI usage jumps from 8 to 81 applications in one year; AI factory funded**\n\nThe number of GenAI applications deployed in the Dutch central government grew from 8 to 81 in a single year, driven largely by municipal chatbots and internal AI assistants. Separately, EU funding has been awarded for a Dutch **AI factory** ŌĆö a national compute cluster (supercomputer expected at full capacity in 2027) dedicated to training and running AI models. An AI expertise centre also starts in 2026. For developers working on public sector AI products, this is meaningful: demand and infrastructure are both scaling fast in the Netherlands.\n\n---\n\nSources:\n- [AI Models in April 2026: Every Major Release](https://renovateqr.com/blog/ai-models-april-2026)\n- [New AI Model Releases March 2026: GPT-5.4, Gemini 3.1, Claude 4.6 & More](https://renovateqr.com/blog/ai-model-releases-2026)\n- [The 2026 MCP Roadmap | Model Context Protocol Blog](http://blog.modelcontextprotocol.io/posts/2026-mcp-roadmap/)\n- [AI Coding Assistants April 2026: Rankings and Review](https://www.digitalapplied.com/blog/ai-coding-assistants-april-2026-cursor-copilot-claude)\n- [Dutch IT Channel ŌĆö Coalitieakkoord 2026: Digitale soevereiniteit versus AI-hype](https://www.dutchitchannel.nl/news/723867/coalitieakkoord-2026-digitale-soevereiniteit-versus-ai-hype)\n- [Dutch Government's Growing Use of Artificial Intelligence](https://www.nldigitalgovernment.nl/news/dutch-governments-growing-use-of-artificial-intelligence/)\n- [Netherlands gets AI factory, European funding awarded | SURF.nl](https://www.surf.nl/en/news/netherlands-gets-ai-factory-european-funding-awarded)\n- [Ōé¼204 Million in EU Funding Available for Digital Innovation Projects](https://www.nldigitalgovernment.nl/news/e204-million-in-eu-funding-available-for-digital-innovation-projects/)"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a90af972839059912 (use SendMessage with to: 'a90af972839059912' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 19228\ntool_uses: 7\nduration_ms: 71967</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"808108e8-5f77-4c63-a64b-a1ed27ddfc09","uuid":"06b4ef99-798a-4c79-a645-00d7b1b90551","timestamp":"2026-04-03T15:07:48.993Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Search for trending AI and tech news from the past week (around 2026-03-30 to 2026-04-03) that would be relevant for a Dutch software developer / CTO working in the public sector and AI agents space. The target audience is developers and tech leads in the Arnhem-Nijmegen region of the Netherlands, AI/ML engineers, and startup CTOs.\n\nJoeri's stack: Next.js, TypeScript, AWS/Azure, AI agents, public sector digitalization, agentic workflows (he builds with Paperclip / agent orchestration tools).\n\nSearch for:\n1. Major AI news (new models, agent frameworks, tooling releases)\n2. Dutch tech/public sector digitalization news\n3. Developer tooling / AI coding assistant news\n\nFind 3-5 strong news items and briefly summarize each (2-3 sentences). Focus on concrete, practical topics ŌĆö not hype. Skip Python-specific news unless it's a broader AI story.\n\nUse web search to find current news.","agentId":"a90af972839059912","agentType":"general-purpose","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here is the weekly tech briefing for the week of 2026-03-30 to 2026-04-03:\n\n---\n\n## Tech News Briefing ŌĆö Week of 30 March ŌĆō 3 April 2026\n\n---\n\n**1. Frontier model war: GPT-5.4, Gemini 3.1, and Claude updates all land in March**\n\nOpenAI shipped GPT-5.4 (March 5) with record scores on computer-use and knowledge-work benchmarks ŌĆö API pricing at $2.50/M input tokens for the standard tier. Google countered with Gemini 3.1 Pro, which leads 13 of 16 major benchmarks and runs at roughly one-third of GPT-5.4's API cost due to a new compression algorithm that cuts memory needs sixfold. Anthropic's Claude Sonnet 4.6 (the model powering this response) is currently topping the GDPval-AA Elo leaderboard, performing at near-Opus quality at Sonnet pricing ŌĆö directly relevant for cost-efficient agentic workloads.\n\n---\n\n**2. MCP ecosystem crosses 6,400 registered servers ŌĆö 2026 roadmap focuses on enterprise readiness**\n\nThe Model Context Protocol now has over 6,400 servers in its official registry and is running in production at enterprises at scale. The published 2026 roadmap addresses gaps that matter for production agentic systems: better Streamable HTTP for remote server deployments (load balancer compatibility, session handling), improved Task primitive lifecycle semantics (retry, expiry), and enterprise requirements like audit trails, SSO-integrated auth, and gateway configuration portability. For anyone building orchestration layers on top of MCP, the direction is clear: the protocol is moving from prototype to production-grade infrastructure.\n\n---\n\n**3. GitHub Copilot agent mode reaches GA across VS Code and JetBrains; Cursor ships Composer 2**\n\nCopilot's agent mode is now generally available in VS Code and JetBrains, and agentic code review shipped in March ŌĆö it can now act on review feedback autonomously. Separately, Cursor shipped Composer 2 on March 19, built on Moonshot AI's Kimi K2.5 with heavy reinforcement learning fine-tuning; it's Cursor's bet that purpose-built coding models beat general LLMs on dev tasks. The emerging developer consensus in 2026: Cursor for daily editing, Claude Code for complex multi-file work and delegation-style tasks.\n\n---\n\n**4. Dutch 2026 coalition agreement: digital sovereignty and a new Dutch Digital Service**\n\nThe new Dutch coalition agreement (presented this week) puts digital autonomy front and center, including a mandate to establish a **Dutch Digital Service** ŌĆö a central body with enforcement power over government ICT choices. This is a direct response to dependency on US hyperscalers and fragmented government IT. For public sector tech leads in the Arnhem-Nijmegen region, this signals upcoming procurement and architecture shifts, particularly around cloud strategy and open-source alignment.\n\n---\n\n**5. Dutch government generative AI usage jumps from 8 to 81 applications in one year; AI factory funded**\n\nThe number of GenAI applications deployed in the Dutch central government grew from 8 to 81 in a single year, driven largely by municipal chatbots and internal AI assistants. Separately, EU funding has been awarded for a Dutch **AI factory** ŌĆö a national compute cluster (supercomputer expected at full capacity in 2027) dedicated to training and running AI models. An AI expertise centre also starts in 2026. For developers working on public sector AI products, this is meaningful: demand and infrastructure are both scaling fast in the Netherlands.\n\n---\n\nSources:\n- [AI Models in April 2026: Every Major Release](https://renovateqr.com/blog/ai-models-april-2026)\n- [New AI Model Releases March 2026: GPT-5.4, Gemini 3.1, Claude 4.6 & More](https://renovateqr.com/blog/ai-model-releases-2026)\n- [The 2026 MCP Roadmap | Model Context Protocol Blog](http://blog.modelcontextprotocol.io/posts/2026-mcp-roadmap/)\n- [AI Coding Assistants April 2026: Rankings and Review](https://www.digitalapplied.com/blog/ai-coding-assistants-april-2026-cursor-copilot-claude)\n- [Dutch IT Channel ŌĆö Coalitieakkoord 2026: Digitale soevereiniteit versus AI-hype](https://www.dutchitchannel.nl/news/723867/coalitieakkoord-2026-digitale-soevereiniteit-versus-ai-hype)\n- [Dutch Government's Growing Use of Artificial Intelligence](https://www.nldigitalgovernment.nl/news/dutch-governments-growing-use-of-artificial-intelligence/)\n- [Netherlands gets AI factory, European funding awarded | SURF.nl](https://www.surf.nl/en/news/netherlands-gets-ai-factory-european-funding-awarded)\n- [Ōé¼204 Million in EU Funding Available for Digital Innovation Projects](https://www.nldigitalgovernment.nl/news/e204-million-in-eu-funding-available-for-digital-innovation-projects/)"}],"totalDurationMs":71967,"totalTokens":19228,"totalToolUseCount":7,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1968,"cache_read_input_tokens":16008,"output_tokens":1251,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1968},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_019T5465TMChxsaCzFRRxiCk","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Excellent! I have great material. Now let me craft 2-3 content hooks from this. The best candidates for Joeri are:\n\n1. **MCP 2026 roadmap** ŌĆö Joeri builds agentic systems, MCP is directly in his stack. The 6,400 servers + production-readiness roadmap is concrete and interesting.\n\n2. **Dutch Digital Service / coalitieakkoord** ŌĆö Joeri works in public sector tech, this is very relevant. The Dutch government mandating digital sovereignty and a central ICT body is a big deal.\n\n\n3. **GenAI in Dutch government 8ŌåÆ81 apps** ŌĆö Also very relevant for Joeri's positioning. Concrete numbers + AI factory shows the market is heating up fast.\n\nThe MCP angle is the strongest tech hook and fits \"Nieuws + jouw take\" perfectly since Joeri can speak from direct experience building agentic workflows. The Dutch Digital Service is strong for public sector positioning, and the 8ŌåÆ81 GenAI apps gives us concrete local numbers that demonstrate momentum. Now I'm structuring these into proper hooks following the HEARTBEAT format with the news angle and draft post concept.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1678,"cache_read_input_tokens":31721,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1678},"output_tokens":20,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"808108e8-5f77-4c63-a64b-a1ed27ddfc09","uuid":"eccabfbd-0e8c-4c63-bf03-1309716d39e4"}
