{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01RFi2B3v2EkTE84GbbmsfQb","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"**Dataview works!** The Debug dashboard shows everything:\n\n- **Test 1**: Lists all files in the vault (Debug, People & Companies, MEMORY, summary files, etc.)\n- **Test 2**: 34 files with frontmatter ŌĆö shows entities (Nox's Joeri Smits, Webbio, joeri-dev), daily notes, knowledge indexes, projects, the test-entity ŌĆö all with correct `type` and `agent` fields\n- **Test 3**: 32 files with tags ŌĆö shows `people`, `company`, `project`, `daily`, etc.\n\nSo Dataview IS working and CAN see all the files. The entity files show up with `type: entity` and agents like Nox, Mitch. The issue must have been the `FROM` clause I used earlier, or the user was previously in source view. Now that they're in reading view, everything renders.\n\nThe main dashboards should also work now since I simplified their queries. Let me post the good news and mark done."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1370,"cache_read_input_tokens":96882,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1370},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"441920ca-57e2-4d9f-8021-cbdca58bc1a4","uuid":"fb68797c-9d2f-4260-a774-f44bc157468c"}
