paperclip$, $paperclip$local_file$paperclip$, $paperclip$712f694b-097f-4ca4-b161-f299187ec27d/7d8b001d-912c-4f3d-a5f4-77195261fac8/57bc2c01-6a94-4394-b173-7ff3b47308f9.ndjson$paperclip$, $paperclip$238027$paperclip$, $paperclip$79637d59ad3801766afd5ef49fc8223c6f66c4e67632dd74507f6f47b0a2587c$paperclip$, false, $paperclip$ configured but never used. The script generates draft JSON files but doesn't POST worklogs to the Tempo API. If the original OpenClaw approach was draft-only too, this needs documenting; otherwise, the submission step is missing.\n\n3. **AC deviation: launchd plist vs Paperclip scheduled trigger** ŌĆö AC says \"Create a Paperclip cron trigger.\" Delivery uses a macOS launchd plist instead. If this was a deliberate choice (Paperclip triggers not suited for this), it should be documented. Otherwise, the `schedule` skill should be used.\n\nI'll reject back to Mitch with these findings."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":923,"cache_read_input_tokens":42561,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":923},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8ff12b75-c91f-4e1f-a8c8-5f0e941db5fa","uuid":"c7bfc8e2-a643-4586-af94-7c650e28a5e3"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01TeUv6Km47r1r5KWwMeZ25b","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01VZJkA9TQULoKjgKB9niLog","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"curl -s -X PATCH \\\n  -H \"Authorization: Bearer $PAPERCLIP_API_KEY\" \\\n  -H \"X-Paperclip-Run-Id: $PAPERCLIP_RUN_ID\" \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\n    \"status\": \"todo\",\n    \"assigneeAgentId\": \"467192bf-0ffd-49de-b18f-91a35b60e57a\",\n    \"comment\": \"## QA Review ŌĆö Rejected\\n\\nGood migration overall, but found issues that need fixing before this can pass.\\n\\n### Blocking Issues\\n\\n**1. Calendar timezone hardcoded to CET (+01:00)**\\n- `tempo-reconstruct.sh` lines 249-250: `start = f\\\"{day.isoformat()}T00:00:00+01:00\\\"`\\n- Netherlands is currently CEST (+02:00). The `tz_name` parameter is passed to `calendar_events_for_day()` but never used for the offset.\\n- **Fix:** Derive the UTC offset from `tz_name` dynamically, e.g. use `ZoneInfo(tz_name)` to compute the correct offset for the target date.\\n\\n**2. No Tempo API submission ŌĆö AC incomplete**\\n- AC says \\\"Implement the Tempo API integration to fetch and log hours.\\\"\\n- `tempo-config.json` has `tempo.token` configured but the script never uses it. Output is draft JSON only.\\n- **Fix:** Either add a Tempo API POST step to submit the worklogs, or document explicitly that this is intentionally draft-only (matching OpenClaw behavior) and update the AC accordingly.\\n\\n### Question\\n\\n**3. launchd plist vs Paperclip scheduled trigger**\\n- AC says \\\"Create a Paperclip cron trigger.\\\" Delivery uses a macOS launchd plist.\\n- If this was deliberate (Paperclip triggers not suited for local cron scripts), add a comment explaining why. Otherwise, consider using the Paperclip `schedule` system.\\n\\n### What passed\\n- Code quality: clean Python, proper error handling, no hardcoded secrets\\n- GitHub/Jira integration: well-implemented with pagination and changelog parsing\\n- Time allocation algorithm: weighted scoring with 15m quantization works correctly\\n- Test output: valid JSON, correct structure\\n\\n@Mitch\"\n  }' \\\n  \"$PAPERCLIP_API_URL/api/issues/87a980a0-33ff-4de8-b498-5a51f5725c07\" | python3 -m json.tool","description":"Reject JOEA-10 back to Mitch with QA feedback"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":923,"cache_read_input_tokens":42561,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":923},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8ff12b75-c91f-4e1f-a8c8-5f0e941db5fa","uuid":"54ac5b61-cc83-47e6-ba84-4304ca55b046"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01VZJkA9TQULoKjgKB9niLog","type":"tool_result","content":"{\n    \"id\": \"87a980a0-33ff-4de8-b498-5a51f5725c07\",\n    \"companyId\": \"712f694b-097f-4ca4-b161-f299187ec27d\",\n    \"projectId\": \"2d1aac53-a8ad-4685-9db7-0fcf2e80fc4d\",\n    \"projectWorkspaceId\": null,\n    \"goalId\": \"a85d1f2d-bd31-46a0-b36a-022c0ebb9921\",\n    \"parentId\": null,\n    \"title\": \"Migrate Tempo hours logging cron to Paperclip\",\n    \"description\": \"In OpenClaw, a cron job ran periodically to log Joeri's hours from Tempo into the system. Migrate this to a Paperclip scheduled trigger.\\n\\nAcceptance criteria:\\n- [ ] Identify how the Tempo hours cron worked in OpenClaw (API calls, schedule, output)\\n- [ ] Create a Paperclip cron trigger that fires on the same schedule\\n- [ ] Implement the Tempo API integration to fetch and log hours\\n- [ ] Verify output matches what OpenClaw produced\\n\\nTempo integration uses the Tempo API. Previous implementation is in the OpenClaw codebase.\",\n    \"status\": \"todo\",\n    \"priority\": \"high\",\n    \"assigneeAgentId\": \"467192bf-0ffd-49de-b18f-91a35b60e57a\",\n    \"assigneeUserId\": null,\n    \"checkoutRunId\": null,\n    \"executionRunId\": \"57bc2c01-6a94-4394-b173-7ff3b47308f9\",\n    \"executionAgentNameKey\": \"tommy\",\n    \"executionLockedAt\": \"2026-04-03T15:07:23.417Z\",\n    \"createdByAgentId\": \"494851cd-3a4d-438f-9ec5-5e37e8d7e54c\",\n    \"createdByUserId\": null,\n    \"issueNumber\": 10,\n    \"identifier\": \"JOEA-10\",\n    \"originKind\": \"manual\",\n    \"originId\": null,\n    \"originRunId\": null,\n    \"requestDepth\": 0,\n    \"billingCode\": null,\n    \"assigneeAdapterOverrides\": null,\n    \"executionWorkspaceId\": null,\n    \"executionWorkspacePreference\": null,\n    \"executionWorkspaceSettings\": null,\n    \"startedAt\": \"2026-04-03T15:08:19.347Z\",\n    \"completedAt\": null,\n    \"cancelledAt\": null,\n    \"hiddenAt\": null,\n    \"createdAt\": \"2026-04-03T14:46:52.502Z\",\n    \"updatedAt\": \"2026-04-03T15:09:53.843Z\",\n    \"labels\": [],\n    \"labelIds\": [],\n    \"comment\": {\n        \"id\": \"93ec2c10-9672-491f-8bb7-832b763ce16e\",\n        \"companyId\": \"712f694b-097f-4ca4-b161-f299187ec27d\",\n        \"issueId\": \"87a980a0-33ff-4de8-b498-5a51f5725c07\",\n        \"authorAgentId\": \"7d8b001d-912c-4f3d-a5f4-77195261fac8\",\n        \"authorUserId\": null,\n        \"body\": \"## QA Review \\u2014 Rejected\\n\\nGood migration overall, but found issues that need fixing before this can pass.\\n\\n### Blocking Issues\\n\\n**1. Calendar timezone hardcoded to CET (+01:00)**\\n- `tempo-reconstruct.sh` lines 249-250: `start = f\\\"{day.isoformat()}T00:00:00+01:00\\\"`\\n- Netherlands is currently CEST (+02:00). The `tz_name` parameter is passed to `calendar_events_for_day()` but never used for the offset.\\n- **Fix:** Derive the UTC offset from `tz_name` dynamically, e.g. use `ZoneInfo(tz_name)` to compute the correct offset for the target date.\\n\\n**2. No Tempo API submission \\u2014 AC incomplete**\\n- AC says \\\"Implement the Tempo API integration to fetch and log hours.\\\"\\n- `tempo-config.json` has `tempo.token` configured but the script never uses it. Output is draft JSON only.\\n- **Fix:** Either add a Tempo API POST step to submit the worklogs, or document explicitly that this is intentionally draft-only (matching OpenClaw behavior) and update the AC accordingly.\\n\\n### Question\\n\\n**3. launchd plist vs Paperclip scheduled trigger**\\n- AC says \\\"Create a Paperclip cron trigger.\\\" Delivery uses a macOS launchd plist.\\n- If this was deliberate (Paperclip triggers not suited for local cron scripts), add a comment explaining why. Otherwise, consider using the Paperclip `schedule` system.\\n\\n### What passed\\n- Code quality: clean Python, proper error handling, no hardcoded secrets\\n- GitHub/Jira integration: well-implemented with pagination and changelog parsing\\n- Time allocation algorithm: weighted scoring with 15m quantization works correctly\\n- Test output: valid JSON, correct structure\\n\\n@Mitch\",\n        \"createdAt\": \"2026-04-03T15:09:53.847Z\",\n        \"updatedAt\": \"2026-04-03T15:09:53.847Z\"\n    }\n}","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8ff12b75-c91f-4e1f-a8c8-5f0e941db5fa","uuid":"4ac518de-a763-41b3-87e3-4f1f7f00f726","timestamp":"2026-04-03T15:09:53.872Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"{\n    \"id\": \"87a980a0-33ff-4de8-b498-5a51f5725c07\",\n    \"companyId\": \"712f694b-097f-4ca4-b161-f299187ec27d\",\n    \"projectId\": \"2d1aac53-a8ad-4685-9db7-0fcf2e80fc4d\",\n    \"projectWorkspaceId\": null,\n    \"goalId\": \"a85d1f2d-bd31-46a0-b36a-022c0ebb9921\",\n    \"parentId\": null,\n    \"title\": \"Migrate Tempo hours logging cron to Paperclip\",\n    \"description\": \"In OpenClaw, a cron job ran periodically to log Joeri's hours from Tempo into the system. Migrate this to a Paperclip scheduled trigger.\\n\\nAcceptance criteria:\\n- [ ] Identify how the Tempo hours cron worked in OpenClaw (API calls, schedule, output)\\n- [ ] Create a Paperclip cron trigger that fires on the same schedule\\n- [ ] Implement the Tempo API integration to fetch and log hours\\n- [ ] Verify output matches what OpenClaw produced\\n\\nTempo integration uses the Tempo API. Previous implementation is in the OpenClaw codebase.\",\n    \"status\": \"todo\",\n    \"priority\": \"high\",\n    \"assigneeAgentId\": \"467192bf-0ffd-49de-b18f-91a35b60e57a\",\n    \"assigneeUserId\": null,\n    \"checkoutRunId\": null,\n    \"executionRunId\": \"57bc2c01-6a94-4394-b173-7ff3b47308f9\",\n    \"executionAgentNameKey\": \"tommy\",\n    \"executionLockedAt\": \"2026-04-03T15:07:23.417Z\",\n    \"createdByAgentId\": \"494851cd-3a4d-438f-9ec5-5e37e8d7e54c\",\n    \"createdByUserId\": null,\n    \"issueNumber\": 10,\n    \"identifier\": \"JOEA-10\",\n    \"originKind\": \"manual\",\n    \"originI