{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Rn5vShK9HHPCQEUsPnMKMu","type":"tool_result","content":"{\n    \"issue\": {\n        \"id\": \"249cfc8e-dac9-4b25-ac6b-be20db5ee1c7\",\n        \"identifier\": \"JOEA-23\",\n        \"title\": \"Design Obsidian \\u2192 content pipeline: transcript intake to LinkedIn draft\",\n        \"description\": \"Joeri wants a clear, low-friction workflow where meeting transcripts land in Obsidian and flow toward LinkedIn posts via Rex.\\n\\n**Context:** Obsidian vault is already connected. The gap is structure and process \\u2014 Joeri needs to know exactly where to drop a transcript, and Rex needs a predictable intake format to analyse and generate LinkedIn hooks from.\\n\\n**Deliverable:**\\n- Propose a folder/template structure in Obsidian for meeting transcripts and knowledge notes\\n- Define the handoff format from Obsidian to Rex (what Rex expects as input)\\n- Map the full pipeline: transcript \\u2192 Obsidian \\u2192 Rex analysis \\u2192 LinkedIn post draft \\u2192 Buffer\\n- Identify any tooling gaps (e.g. does Rex need a new plugin or ingestion route?)\\n\\nOutput: a short design doc (plan document on this issue) that Joeri and Mitch can act on.\\n\\n**Goal:** Advance the Obsidian knowledge base goal \\u2014 build a content and knowledge pipeline that feeds LinkedIn posts in Buffer, growing Joeris reach and thought leadership.\",\n        \"status\": \"todo\",\n        \"priority\": \"high\",\n        \"projectId\": null,\n        \"goalId\": \"462a654a-c009-4734-bc21-508211efd923\",\n        \"parentId\": null,\n        \"assigneeAgentId\": \"7d8b001d-912c-4f3d-a5f4-77195261fac8\",\n        \"assigneeUserId\": null,\n        \"updatedAt\": \"2026-04-03T15:07:35.422Z\"\n    },\n    \"ancestors\": [],\n    \"project\": null,\n    \"goal\": {\n        \"id\": \"462a654a-c009-4734-bc21-508211efd923\",\n        \"title\": \"Knowledge base in Obsidian voor het delen van kennis\",\n        \"status