INSERT INTO "public"."issue_comments" ("id", "company_id", "issue_id", "author_agent_id", "author_user_id", "body", "created_at", "updated_at") VALUES ($paperclip$57d1bb17-1f58-418e-8270-4ff9c621d26e$paperclip$, $paperclip$712f694b-097f-4ca4-b161-f299187ec27d$paperclip$, $paperclip$a0e60976-a292-4234-936e-57334713103c$paperclip$, $paperclip$467192bf-0ffd-49de-b18f-91a35b60e57a$paperclip$, NULL, $paperclip$## Done ŌĆö News digest migrated to Paperclip

Migrated the OpenClaw "Nieuws Digest ŌĆö nu.nl" cron to standalone Paperclip automation.

**What was built:**
- `news-digest.py` ŌĆö Python script (stdlib only, no pip deps) that fetches 6 RSS feeds (nu.nl, NOS, Tweakers, BBC), scores items by keyword relevance (politics/economy/tech boosted, sports/royals/celebrity filtered), deduplicates, and posts top 6-8 items to Discord channel `1478050132749455411`
- `news-config.json` ŌĆö Discord bot token + channel config
- `run-news-cron.sh` ŌĆö Wrapper with logging (30-day retention)
- `nl.webbio.paperclip.news-cron.plist` ŌĆö launchd plist, daily at 08:30 local time

**Key changes vs OpenClaw version:**
- Rule-based curation instead of Claude Haiku (the AI version was timing out with consecutive errors)
- Standalone Python with zero pip dependencies
- Discord 2000-char limit handled with auto-truncation
- Same RSS sources, same schedule, same Discord channel

**Tested:**
- Dry run: 102 items fetched, 8 selected, formatting verified
- Live test: successfully posted digest to Discord

**To install the launchd cron:**
```
cp nl.webbio.paperclip.news-cron.plist ~/Library/LaunchAgents/
launchctl load ~/Library/LaunchAgents/nl.webbio.paperclip.news-cron.plist
```

