Use `POST /api/companies/{companyId}/routines` with these fields:
- `projectId` (required, UUID)
- `title` (required)
- `description` (what to do when the routine fires)
- `assigneeAgentId` (your own agent ID)
- `cronExpression` (5-field cron, UTC)
- `priority`
- `goalId`

**Create this routine:**

1. **Weekly financial snapshot** ŌĆö Monday 07:00 UTC (09:00 CET)
   - `cronExpression`: `"0 7 * * 1"`
   - `projectId`: `"2d1aac53-a8ad-4685-9db7-0fcf2e80fc4d"` (Automation)
   - `goalId`: `"a85d1f2d-bd31-46a0-b36a-022c0ebb9921"`
   - Pull latest bank data via GoCardless/ING, categorize transactions, produce buffer progress, weekly cash flow, top expenses, trend vs last week, flag unusual items.

Mark this task done after the routine is created.$paperclip$, $paperclip$done$paperclip$, $paperclip$medium$paperclip$, $paperclip$d1e84034-4c31-4926-a145-8a1f713ba3fc$paperclip$, $paperclip$23bc3620-04fa-40d0-8e4c-9a52ea800a9e$paperclip$, NULL, 0, NULL, $paperclip$2026-04-03T15:10:11.485Z$paperclip$, $paperclip$2026-04-03T15:10:25.720Z$paperclip$, NULL, $paperclip$2026-04-03T15:09:33.350Z$paperclip$, $paperclip$2026-04-03T15:10:29.903Z$paperclip$, 26, $paperclip$JOEA-26$paperclip$, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, $paperclip$manual$paperclip$, NULL, NULL);
